
PLAYER_EXISTS(1)                                 PLAYER_EXISTS(1)

NAME
       player_exists() - returns true if a given player exists

SYNOPSIS
       int player_exists(string str)

DESCRIPTION
       If the argument passed is an existing player name, this function
       returns true.  Otherwise the function returns false.

EXAMPLES
       player_exists("descartes") returns true or false

LOCATION
       /secure/SimulEfun/user_functions.c

SEE ALSO
       account_exists()

                                                                1
